This plugin will split a single line function call so that every argument is on
its own line.

Example:

  foo(really_long_arg_name1, really_long_arg_name2, really_long_arg_name3)

Becomes:

  foo(
    really_long_arg_name1,
    really_long_arg_name2,
    really_long_arg_name3
  )

To run the plugin map a key combo in your vimrc like this:

  nnoremap <silent> <Leader>sa :call ArgsSplit()<CR>

Then run the ArgsSplit() function on the line you wish to split.

This plugin requires Vim to be compiled with Ruby support.

To install use Pathogen or Vundle, or drop plugin/args_split.vim in your plugin 
directory.
